– The Orlando Pirates hard tackler was caught driving at 223km/h in a 120km/h
zone. The Randburg Magistrate’s Court sentenced him to community service.4. Bobby Motaung
– The Kaizer Chiefs boss was reportedly in danger of losing his Bentley and
also a petrol station in Jozi. The cases are ongoing.5. Tumisho Masha
was accused of being a woman basher by his estranged wife Zozibini. He appeared
in the Randburg Magistrate’s Court last month.6. Mandla N – Sunday Sun reported that Mandla N had
approached the high court in Jozi and accused his wife Tumi of stealing R2
million.7. Matthews Phosa
– The former Mpumalanga premier accused an Australian company of not paying
him. The South Gauteng High Court issued an order in his favour.8. Kelly Khumalo
– Sunday Sun reported that the star
was slapped with a R41 000 court judgment for failing to perform at a Botswana
gig.9. Brickz –
The kwaito superstar (real name Sipho Ndlovu) got a 15-year sentence for raping
his niece. His lawyers told the press he would appeal the judgment.10. Arthur
Mafokate – Dubbed the King of Kwaito, Mafokate has been in and out of
courtrooms lately for allegedly assaulting his ex-girlfriend and singer Cici. And
Mafokate laid counter charges against her.11. Thato Molamu
– The TV star was arrested for speeding in Pretoria. But he put up a fight to
prove his innocence, and the charge was withdrawn.  
